<div style="margin: 10px 0 0 10px; width: 425px;">
<p style="font-size: 24px; color: #76add1; margin: 0 10px 0 0;">The Student Activities program is about giving students the  opportunity to learn and grow through taking action. As students  organize dances, concerts, sporting events, and service projects, they  develop into the best, most capable versions of themselves.</p>
<p>Within Activities, students are participants, not just spectators.  Over 200 student organizations within the six core areas of Outdoor,  Social, Service, Talent, Fitness, and Sports provide opportunities for  participants to grow. Students choose their level of commitment&mdash;whether  it&rsquo;s coaching a basketball team, teaching a weekend dance class, or  organizing a campus-wide event.</p>
<p>If you want to learn about more ways to get involved at BYU-Idaho, click <a href="http://www.byui.edu/getinvolved/#home" target="_self">here</a>.</p>
